<p><a href="x77.xml">Visit BETA site </a><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></p>]]></IntroCopy></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Optional Content" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<div class="cwrap">
<div class="ccl">
<p><strong>Global search bar </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Every page has a global search bar in the header to search all public BYU-Idaho sites.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<img alt="Search" height="166" src="Images/Admin_Offices/university_communications/campaigns/beta_campaign/search/search.jpg" title="Search in college depts" width="435" /></div>
<div class="cwrap">
<div class="ccl">
<p><strong>Local search bar </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Department and office sub-sites have a their own search bar that searches only their information.</li>
<li>The results from this search bar will be much more refined and helpful if you know which site to search in.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<img alt="Global Search" height="185" src="Images/Admin_Offices/university_communications/campaigns/beta_campaign/search/topSearch.jpg" title="Search Globally" width="435" /></div>
<div class="cwrap">
<div class="ccl">
<p><strong>Google Mini</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Google Mini has been adopted as BYU-Idaho's new search engine-a major improvement from the previous search function.</li>
<li>The new site is better optimized for search indexing and should, over time, provide better results to all engines.</li>
</ul>
</div>
